\boxed{\binom{50}{25}^2}

Few-sentence justification:
Split the 100×100 board into 50×50 blocks of size 2×2; since 2500 kings = number of blocks, exactly one per block. To avoid vertical attacks, in each block-column all kings must lie in the same row (top or bottom); to avoid horizontal attacks, in each block-row all kings must lie in the same column (left or right). Thus choose which 25 of the 50 block-columns are top (the rest bottom) and which 25 of the 50 block-rows are left (the rest right), giving C(50,25)^2 arrangements.
